<div class="Sections">

	<section class="Manchet">
		<h1>Sign up <small>to Radio4000</small></h1>
		<p class="u-tc">Create an account to start with your radio</p>
	</section>

	<section class="Section">
		<div class="Grid Grid--center">
			<div class="Grid-cell Grid-cell--double">
				<div class="Container Container--small">
					{{user-signup onSignup=(action "signup")}}

					<p>
						Already have a radio? <a href="{{href-to 'auth.login'}}">Log in</a>.<br>
					</p>
					<p>
						Have a question? <a href="{{href-to 'about.contact'}}">Contact us</a>.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="Grid-cell Grid-cell--double">
				<div class="Container">
					<p>
						<em>"Alright, but why should I start a radio?!"</em>
					</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Radio4000 is open to everyone, no special skills or knowledge required</li>
						<li>Create and manage your music selection in your radio</li>
						<li>Quickly add music to your radio, directly from YouTube videos</li>
						<li>Organise your music with #hashtags, dig deeper to understand your discoveries</li>
						<li>Play custom selections of music in any radio (anyone can suggest their favorite selections)</li>
						<li>Share and embed every radio, anywhere online</li>
						<li>Export all your data, make backups and use it with other softwares</li>
					</ul>

					<p>More reasons?</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Start a peaceful experiment, Radio4000 is designed to be non-intrusive software. There are no notifications here ({{link-to 'read more in the introduction' 'about.intro'}})</li>
						<li>It's free and <a href="https://github.com/internet4000/radio4000" target="_blank" rel="noopener">open source</a></li>
						<li>Your radio is as anonymous as you want it, it is about music</li>
						<li>Discover and support underground and upcoming artists in the context of music you like</li>
						<li>Explore other people's selection, we're already many sharing our favorite tunes</li>
						<li>Favorite and follow other radio channels</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</div>
